#1st re-asked

To make your tool available across these platforms, you essentially need to distribute your code (or a pre-compiled binary) and then provide "recipes" for each package manager to find and install it.

## 1. curl (Shell Script Installer)

Create an install.sh script and host it on your site or [GitHub](https://github.com/). It should detect the OS, download your tool, and move it to the user's PATH. [1, 2]

- Template:

#!/bin/bash# install.sh
OS="$(uname -s)"
ARCH="$(uname -m)"
INSTALL_DIR="/usr/local/bin"

echo "Installing your-tool for $OS-$ARCH..."# 1. Download binary from GitHub Releases or your server# 2. Extract if necessary# 3. Move to /usr/local/bin# Example:
curl -L "https://github.com" -o "$INSTALL_DIR/your-tool"
chmod +x "$INSTALL_DIR/your-tool"
echo "Done! Run 'your-tool' to start."

- Method: Host this at ://yourdomain.com so users can run curl -fsSL ://yourdomain.com | bash. [1]

## 2. npm & bun

Both use the same package.json logic. You publish your code to the npm registry. [3]

- Template (package.json):

{
"name": "your-tool-name",
"version": "1.0.0",
"bin": {
"your-command": "./dist/index.js"
},
"scripts": {
"build": "bun build ./index.ts --outdir ./dist"
}
}

- Docs: Ensure your entry file starts with #!/usr/bin/env node (or #!/usr/bin/env bun). Run npm publish to make it available for npm install -g or bun install -g. [4, 5]

## 3. brew (Homebrew Tap) [5, 6]

Create a new GitHub repository named homebrew-tap and add a "Formula." [7, 8]

- Template (Formula/your-tool.rb):

class YourTool < Formula
desc "A short description of your tool"
homepage "https://yourdomain.com"
url "https://github.com"
sha256 "REPLACE_WITH_SHA256_OF_TARBALL"

def install
bin.install "your-tool"
endend

- Method: Users run brew tap user/tap then brew install your-tool. [8, 9, 10]

## 4. paru (Arch User Repository)

Create a PKGBUILD file and upload it to the AUR. [11, 12]

- Template (PKGBUILD):

pkgname=your-tool-name
pkgver=1.0.0
pkgrel=1
pkgdesc="Description of your tool"
arch=('x86_64')
url="https://yourdomain.com"
license=('MIT')
source=("https://github.com")
sha256sums=('SKIP') # Replace with actual SHA256

package() {
install -Dm755 "$srcdir/tool-linux" "$pkgdir/usr/bin/your-tool"
}

- Method: Once uploaded to the AUR, users can install it via paru -S your-tool-name. [13, 14]

